The paper deals with the mixed domination problem, which is a graph theory problem. The use of dynamic programming and tree-width in the algorithm suggests that it belongs to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The problem is also related to graph theory and optimization, which are covered by cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
